  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Political and Civic Education Program</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.  3-day training camp in Sindh

2. 3-day training camp in Punjab

3. Two 3-day training camps in Afghanistan

4. 3-day Orientation / Application workshop on  Human Rights and Peace Curriculum in Pakistan

5. 3-day Orientation / Application workshop on  Human Rights and Peace Curriculum in Afghanistan 

6. Exposure visits to different historical and informative places in Sindh administrative buildings

7. Exposure visit to different historical and informative places in Punjab 

8. Distribution of 1000 workbooks in Urdu/Sindhi/Pashtu</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">100 Teachers, 1270 Students</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will be geared towards increasing students&#x2019; and teachers&#x2019; understanding of  current and emerging socio-political issues. It aims to bring about the essential transformation of society with a focus on child and human rights, gender equality, peace building and enabling participation of youth in the politics, social and economic dimensions of their country.</narrative>
  </description>
